<div id="content" lang="en" dir="ltr">
Cages could be introduced as a new type of trapping kits.  A normal cage don't deal damage, but immobilizes a monster that steps on it until the creature breaks free (e.g. for a few turns). Soul cages could even be effective against Demons and non-corporeal beings such as Ghosts. <p>
<a href="./RavenRed">RavenRed</a>: Nice idea. It could go all the way from "snare" (good for catching relatively powerless animals) all the way through "man trap" (good for 'p' and 'h' monsters) to "Soul Cage" (as you say, good for demons and non-corporeals) and Vala Chains (immobilises Morgoth for a turn or two?)... also interesting would be if the monsters could still attack and cast spells whilst immobilised... traps would be therefore good for shoot-and-scoot characters... 
</p>
<p>
<a class="nonexistent" href="./FubarObfusco">FubarObfusco</a>: I like the idea of a mundane (nonmagical) item that can catch and immobilize monsters. A <em>snare</em> is a more realistic approach than a <em>cage</em>, I expect -- a cage that can drop over a large creature is not going to be practical to conceal. Think bear-traps, rope snares, and net snares instead, at various different sizes. I am not sure it would be practical for a rogue to haul around enough chain to fashion a snare for dragons, however. Alternately, consider Trapping as a skill of <em>assembling</em> snares from various mundane objects (sticks, rope, rocks). 
</p>
<p>
Simon: Capturing animals long enough to tame them comes to mind. Carrying animals in cages to sell them too. We have a black market for those. (-; 
</p>
<p>
Solorin: *Sigh* Such a cruel, cruel world. Who's up for chickenfights in Arda? 
</p>
